sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J331004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Helps break down the complex protein of gluten. To use it it should be placed inside a Lactobacillus culture that will then be streaked. This has a chromo protein that reports pink to show if the device has worked.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gilles Yvan Buck
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Has not been tested in any sorts. This is all theory and has not been proven.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1033221
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for a promoter that works in both E. coli and L. bacillus. It is characterized agains J23101, when J23101 had 4322 AU, this promoter had 1913 AU.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephanie Herman, Alona Nyberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a synthetic promoter based on a promoter library from the article "The Sequence of Spacers between the Consensus Sequences Modulates the Strength of Prokaryotic Promoters." by Peter Ruhdal Jensen and Karin Hammer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is designed with the same sticky ends as you would get by cutting it with EcoRI-HF and Spel.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J331002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This helps break down the protein of gluten and degrades it in the stomach.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Gilles Yvan Buck

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: G319S_Tri
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A mutated Kumamolisin-As enzyme aimed to combat celiac disease by increased specificity for the PQLP peptide, an antigenic epitope in gliadin.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sydney Gordon, Daniel Hadidi, Elizabeth Stanley, Sarah Wolf, Angus Toland, Sean Wu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Point mutation at residues 319, 358, and 368 from Glycine to Serine, Aspartate to Glycine, and Aspartate to Histidine, respectively.
